post.description:
Send a user message and receive a streaming response with real-time agent updates.

**Event Types:**
- `agent_thought`: Agent explaining what it's doing (display as thinking/status)
- `data_preview`: Truncated data snippets (display with faint styling)
- `final_response`: The actual answer to display in chat
- `chart`: Chart configuration if data visualization was generated
- `sources`: Source citations from knowledge base
- `tokens`: Token usage statistics
- `error`: Error messages
- `done`: Stream complete signal

**Usage:**
```javascript
const response = await fetch('/chats/{id}/messages/stream', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  body: JSON.stringify({ content: 'What are our Q3 sales?' })
});

const reader = response.body.getReader();
const decoder = new TextDecoder();

while (true) {
  const { done, value } = await reader.read();
  if (done) break;

  const text = decoder.decode(value);
  const lines = text.split('\n\n');

  for (const line of lines) {
    if (line.startsWith('data: ')) {
      const event = JSON.parse(line.slice(6));
      switch (event.type) {
        case 'agent_thought':
          showThinking(event.message);
          break;
        case 'final_response':
          showAnswer(event.content);
          break;
        // ... handle other events
      }
    }
  }
}
```
